challenges: In Wednesday, the glasses really bugged me and I could not wait for the study to end. Over the days I got more comfortable to them, but constantly having something in the face and not being able to remove it (unlike sunglasses) was really unusual for me
beh_adapt: Not much. I didn't wear sunglasses, but was still fulfilling my obligations, e.g., going to work or to the university
social: Many, often the first time with my fellow students resp. colleagues, or at the lone in front of the cashier. But all were positive und sparked curiosity in the study and the research
improvements: Make it smaller / try do omit the glasses
